    <header>
      <p>SUPREME GASTRONOMIC COURT</p>
      <p>First Chamber</p>
      <p>Judgment No. 127/2024</p>
      <p>Constitutional challenge against the <ref href="/akn/poc/act/valencian-paella-recipe-amended">reformed Act No. 42/2023</ref></p>
    </header>

    <judgmentBody>
      <introduction eId="intro">
        <p>In the city of Gastronomia, on September 20, 2024.</p>
        <p>Having considered the complaint filed by the Association of Defenders of Valencian Paella against the reform enacted by the <ref href="/akn/poc/bill/paella-reform-2024">Reform Bill</ref>, debated in the <ref href="/akn/poc/debate/plenary-paella-reform">plenary session of June 15, 2024</ref>.</p>
      </introduction>

      <background eId="antecedentes">
        <heading>Background</heading>
        <paragraph eId="para_1">
          <num>1.</num>
          <content><p><ref href="/akn/poc/act/valencian-paella-recipe">Act No. 42/2023</ref> established the official Valencian Paella recipe with strict requirements on ingredients and cooking method.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_2">
          <num>2.</num>
          <content><p>The <ref href="/akn/poc/bill/paella-reform-2024">Reform Bill</ref> relaxed these requirements, allowing alternatives to several traditional ingredients.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_3">
          <num>3.</num>
          <content><p>The plaintiffs allege that the reform violates the right to gastronomic cultural identity recognized in the Gastronomic Constitution.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
      </background>

      <arguments eId="fundamentos">
        <heading>Legal Grounds</heading>
        <paragraph eId="para_4">
          <num>First.</num>
          <content><p>The right to gastronomic cultural identity is not absolute and must be balanced against the right to accessible food.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_5">
          <num>Second.</num>
          <content><p>The reform does not eliminate the designation 'Valencian Paella' but creates the additional category of 'mixed paella', respecting the technical distinction endorsed by the <ref href="/akn/poc/debate/gastronomy-committee">committee hearing</ref>.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_6">
          <num>Third.</num>
          <content><p>However, the relaxation of the rice type (allowing round-grain rice) DOES affect the essence of the dish according to expert technical opinion.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
      </arguments>

      <decision eId="fallo">
        <heading>Ruling</heading>
        <paragraph eId="para_7">
          <num>1.</num>
          <content><p>The challenge is PARTIALLY DISMISSED. The creation of the 'mixed paella' category is constitutional.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_8">
          <num>2.</num>
          <content><p>The challenge is PARTIALLY UPHELD regarding <ref href="/akn/poc/act/valencian-paella-recipe#art_1">Article 1</ref>. The designation 'Valencian Paella' requires bomba rice as an essential requirement.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph eId="para_9">
          <num>3.</num>
          <content><p>This ruling shall be published in the <ref href="/akn/poc/officialGazette/gastronomy-gazette-2024">Official Gazette of Gastronomia</ref>.</p></content>
        </paragraph>
      </decision>
